    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @jthcc we currently only supports giving a template per hits.\n\nWe are thinking about giving the users the possibility to provide their own full hits template (so you will have to iterate yourself the hits in the template).\n\nWe are not sure right now this would be the best solution.\n\nIn the meantime what you can do is create a custom widget:\n\n``` js\nvar myHitsWidget = {\n  _container: $('#myHits'),\n  getConfiguration: function() {\n    return {\n      hitsPerPage: 50\n    }\n  },\n  init: function() {\n    // if you need some jQuery code here, do it\n  },\n  render: function(args) {\n    var out = '';\n    args.results.hits.forEach(function(hit) {\n      out += '...'; // do whatever you want here, any html structure\n    });\n    this._container.html(html);\n  }\n};\n\nsearch.addWidget(myHitsWidget);\n```\n",
